  "text": "• Chronic implantation of a thermistor probe into the hollow space located above the anterior portion of the nasal cavity. This probe does not penetrate any soft epithelial tissues and allows recording of the respiratory rhythm in awake mice with high precision. It does not damage or irritate the nasal epithelium and is compatible with studies in freely moving animals, as in seizure or epilepsy models. [CITATION_1] • Endotracheal tube. When the animal is anesthetized, spray lidocaine on the endotracheal tube and intubate the animal using transillumination. For more details see Appendix S2 and Ref. 51.",
